          <p>Explain to the class that a complex fraction is actually a division problem in which we first have to simplify numerator and denominator -- a long process that can be made easier with the "short-cut" of multiplying top and bottom by the LCD. Demonstrate with an easy numerical example that we get the same answer with both methods.</p></commentary>

